\section{USING THE PACKAGE}
\label{UsingThePackage}

The programs of the package are located in a directory which should be
placed on the shell search path.  This directory also contains some of
the supporting files.  In our configuration the programs are held in
the directory {\tt /hat/loc/bin} which is set to access the correct
files on both Sun~3 and Sun~4 architectures.  The \LaTeX\ macro files
{\tt hol.sty} and {\tt TQ.sty} are contained in a second directory.
These style files should be made available to \TeX\ and \LaTeX\ by
setting the {\tt TEXINPUTS} environment variable.  This may be done by
including a line based on the following in the C-shell startup file
(\verb"~/.cshrc").

\begin{quote}
{\tt setenv TEXINPUTS .:{\em local-macros\/}:{\em main-macros\/}:}
\end{quote}

Where, {\em local-macros\/} is replaced with the directory containing
{\tt hol.sty} and {\tt TQ.sty}, and {\em main-macros\/} with the
directory holding the standard \TeX\ and \LaTeX\ macro files.  In our
configuration these directories are {\tt /hat/loc/tex/macros} and {\tt
/hat/nih/tex3/inputs} respectively.

Here, the environment variable {\tt TEXINPUTS} contains a colon
separated list of three directories which \TeX\ and \LaTeX\ scan from
the left for any source files they want to read.  Thus, files are
chosen from the current directory (\ie, the ``.'' entry) in preference
to the other directories.

